      "content": "that's a fair summary, but it feels like you're just saying both sides exist. isn't there more to it than just \"opinions\"? like, from a practical standpoint, isn't the idea of healthcare as a human right way more supported by global standards and modern ethics than the idea of it being a market commodity? doesn't that make the \"government takeover\" argument kinda outdated?",
